Practical Lab: Canary Tokens

Hi CyberDefenders,

In this lab, we are going to:

  • Explore how to create a simple decoy file using canarytokens.org to generate a Word file that will send a notification to an email address of your choice once opened.


Canarytokens.org is a set of free tools that help defenders discover they have been breached by having attackers announce themselves.

To create a decoy word file, go to: https://canarytokens.org/generate 

Select Microsoft Word document from the list. 

Figure - zoom in


To receive access notifications, enter your email and add a reminder note.

Figure - zoom in


Click Create my Canarytoken, and your word file will be ready to download.

Figure - zoom in


To try it out, open the word file, and you will receive a notification email containing helpful information such as the source IP address, time, and location.

Figure - zoom in

 

Start Experimenting, See What You Can Do!

As you can see, canarytokens.org makes it easy to deploy tokens instantly. We encourage you to experiment with other token types to know how to utilize this effective tool in your network.

Additional resource:

  • Build Your Own CanaryToken Server - CanaryToken
